Evans12 again. At first, way to high a potential, by about 50 mV, to hit the 100 uA. (recall, 100 uA * 100 Ohm = 10 mV). Flowing through counter (while at OCP) doesn't help. Reattaching crocodile, though, does! Activity seems to pick up where it had left off (unfortunately half of the activity of Evans12 was lost while repeating +1.4 V vs RHE so many times in 16O.) This makes my life simpler. Looks like approx same capacitance as Evans6, but lower activity by a factor of ~3 :( Also, a bit worse background, than Evans6 (down to 60 mV overpotential!) on 19A27.
